Definition of Terms
  
  1. "Software" shall mean any data that acquires input and produces output with the
  use of a computer as well as third-party software.
  
  2. "Redistribution" shall mean the transmission of software to computers that are
  authorized to access by any entity other than the copyright holder(s) of the
  software.
  
  3. "Project" shall mean the files and tools used to build and modify the software,
  including but not limited to, compilers, build scripts, debuggers, and third-party
  software.
  
  4. "Third-party software" shall mean any software included in the project that is
  built by any entity other than the copyright holder(s) of the project.
  
  5. "Third-party contributor" shall mean any entity that has modified the project's
  source files without holding any copyright on the original software. In that case,
  the copyright holder(s) of a project are "third-party contributors" to the third
  

